{"key":"processedPost-7831660","value":{"id":7831660,"first":7830823,"last":7831745,"when":1199471654,"utime":"01/04/08 08:34 PM","content":"For grain jars, I prefer synthetic filter disks, but I don't inoculate grain jars with syringes anyway.  If you do, micropore tape works.  I suggest putting a piece of tape on both the inside and outside of the lid, and then after syringe inoculation, place a third piece of tape over the damaged tape.<br />I've made quite a few pf and rye grain jars this way to test the tek, and I really wish I had included it on the DVD.  It will be on the next one for sure.  It really does make the dry verm barrier obsolete.<br />RR","title":"Re: Micro pore tape instead of Tyvek??"}}